<br>
Looked into some of the velious quest armors; damn they look sweet. From what I've read, the Grand Master armor (Thurgadin) is the easiest to get and lowest on the totem pole. The Golden Star (Kael) is about the middle. And, the White Lotus (Skyshrine) is the top; although just barely.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I figured I'd go for the White Lotus stuff. However, the chest piece from the Golden Star line seems better than the White Lotus piece (+5 AC, +8 sta, at the expense of -7 dex/agi), primarily for the Sta boost (being a difficult stat to raise).<br>
<br>
I figure it must be possible to quest the Golden Star chest piece, then switch factions to get the rest of the White Lotus line up (well, at least the legs and bracers).<br>
<br>
Now, my question is: am I insane? Is this just way too much work to bother for just +8 sta?<br>
<br>
Even further, are these quests worth doing? I looked at the Steel Threaded armor from the Twilight Sea, and even started them, but, oh my, what a PITA.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
- Khadaji<br>
<br>
