<br>
Legs - any. You might wear it if you don't have better, but the effect (Ox) is good. Flayed Baep/Oiled are better.<br>
<br>
Arms - Myself I prefer WL even over Grey Flesh because they have more HP (and my AC is over 1300 raid buffed already). Personal choice.<br>
<br>
BP - Fungus is &quot;better&quot;, and although the effect is nice, you have one very basic problem. Leather BP's &quot;should&quot; always go to druids before any monk, because the usefullness to the guild &quot;clicky RotG&quot; is so much more usefull for them. With FA 3 you can bind to 100% anyway in the same time as clicking this.<br>
<br>
You also say &quot;then switch factions to get the rest&quot;..<br>
<br>
Well, yes. maybe. Some people do, but do you have any idea how long this takes to do ? We're not talking a couple of days, we're talking a couple of weeks of constant/boring faction grind for most people, unless you can get boss mob faction hits (Vindi/Statue/Tormax/AoW... Yeli etc).<br>
<br>
What I'd recommend is going along with the same factions/fights as your guild, and this usually means GM first (killing in Arena), then when you move to ToV White Lotus from HoT, and then if you can be bothered when you eventually switch factions and get Golden Star. However, by the time most people get to this stage they already have better anyway. <p><br>
